---
import SectionLabel from "../../elements/SectionLabel.astro";
import Heading from "../../elements/Heading.astro";
import BodyText from "../../elements/BodyText.astro";
---

<section
  id="organization"
  class="py-28 md:py-40 px-6 bg-rh-warm-light dark:bg-rh-warm-dark"
>
  <div
    class="max-w-7xl mx-auto grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-16 lg:gap-24 items-center"
  >
    <!-- Left Column: The Portrait -->
    <div class="lg:col-span-5 relative">
      <div
        class="w-full aspect-4/5 bg-rh-ink rounded-4xl overflow-hidden relative border border-black/10 dark:border-white/10 shadow-2xl"
      >
        <img
          src="/assets/img/people/the-architect.webp"
          alt="Clark Sell"
          width="800"
          height="1000"
          loading="lazy"
          decoding="async"
          class="absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover grayscale contrast-125 transition-all duration-700 hover:grayscale-0"
        />
        <div
          class="absolute bottom-6 left-6 font-mono text-xs bg-black/80 backdrop-blur-md px-4 py-2 rounded text-rh-chalk border border-white/10 uppercase tracking-widest"
        >
          &gt; ID_VERIFIED
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Right Column: The Narrative -->
    <div class="lg:col-span-7 flex flex-col justify-center">
      <!-- Terminal Header -->
      <SectionLabel text="> SYS.IDENTITY // THE_ARCHITECT" class="mb-8" />

      <!-- Headline -->
      <Heading size="md" class="mb-8 tracking-tight">
        I Built the Code.<br />Then I Built the Culture.
      </Heading>

      <!-- Body Copy -->
      <BodyText class="mb-6"> Hi, I'm Clark Sell. </BodyText>

      <BodyText class="mb-6">
        For 25 years, I engineered complex software ecosystems. I know how to
        build secure, scalable infrastructure. But I quickly realized that the
        most elegant code in the world is useless if the humans using it don't
        feel like they belong.
      </BodyText>

      <BodyText class="mb-6">
        So, I stepped out from behind the terminal. I went on to run one of the
        largest community conferences in the United States, studying exactly how
        thousands of people connect, trust, and build loyalty in the real world.
      </BodyText>

      <BodyText>
        I founded re/Human because the internet is drowning in faked AI
        authority and rented audiences. You don't need another marketer. You
        need an architect who understands both the deep-tech infrastructure and
        the human soul.
      </BodyText>

      <a
        href="/the-architect"
        class="inline-block font-mono text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-rh-ember hover:underline mt-8"
      >
        Read the Full Story →
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
